======================================================================
PART 4: IP zeros — Lee-Yang analysis for P_7
======================================================================

  IP(G(P_7), x) = 7x² + 80x + 1
  Zeros: -0.012514, -11.416058
  Both real and NEGATIVE ✓ (Lee-Yang)
  Product of zeros = c/a = 1/7 = 0.142857
  Sum of zeros = -b/a = -80/7 = -11.428571

  IP(G(P_11), x) = 1155x³ + 10879x² + 21169x + 1
  Zeros:
    x = -6.67207464 (real)
    x = -2.74692574 (real)
    x = -0.00004724 (real)
  All real and negative: ✓

  Distance from x=2 to nearest zero: 2.000047
  We evaluate IP at x=2 (fugacity λ=2), which is past all zeros.
  This is the SUPERCRITICAL regime of the hard-core model.

